description.value: Ionian terracotta figure vase (plastic vase). Partially reconstructed from four joined fragments of upper body of aryballos in form of head of Achelous as bull. Mould-made, with 'black glaze' slip and applied white and red paint. Horns, eyes and ears were black, the beard is indicated by black stripes, and the forehead was outlined with alternate red and white dots, as was the upper part of the eye. The vase mouth rim was decorated on top with a cross. Fine Pale cream fine Ionian clay fabric with sparse fine black inclusions.
